    <name>
      <text>9.4.6 (Find Binomial probability)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>{@perc*100@}% of union members are in favour of a change of their employment conditions. A random sample of {@nn@} members is taken. Find the probability that {@xx@} members are in favour of the change. Give your answer to precisely two significant figures.</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(X\) denote the number of members in the sample in favour of the change. In this case \(n = {@nn@}\) and \(p = {@perc@}\). Thus
\[
X \sim B({@nn@}, {@perc@}). 
\]
We require 
\[
P(X = {@xx@}) = {{@nn@}\choose {@xx@}} ({@perc@})^{@xx@} ({@1-perc@})^{@nn-xx@} = {@ta1@}
\]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
